body_html:
@tensorflowbutler the same issue,
tf:1.7.0
android studio:3.0
os:macos 10.12.6
no egpu and other
used the github demo code from tensorflow/contrib/lite/java/demo.
gpu/cudnn no

I add the tflite into assets,then ./gradlew assembleDebug,terminal tip:
just do this:
Download the quantized Mobilenet TensorFlow Lite model and unzip and copy mobilenet_quant_v1_224.tflite to the assets directory: tensorflow/contrib/lite/java/demo/app/src/main/assets/.

/Users/candrwow/Documents/GitHub/MachineLearning/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/lite/java/demo/app/src/main/java/com/example/android/tflitecamerademo/ImageClassifier.java:152:16: The method setNumThreads(int) is undefined for the type Interpreter
/Users/candrwow/Documents/GitHub/MachineLearning/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/lite/java/demo/app/src/main/java/com/example/android/tflitecamerademo/ImageClassifier.java:177:21: Resource leak: 'inputStream' is never closed
/Users/candrwow/Documents/GitHub/MachineLearning/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/lite/java/demo/app/src/main/java/com/example/android/tflitecamerademo/Camera2BasicFragment.java:61:8: The import android.widget.Toast is never used

I try ./gradlew clean and invalidate cache and restart,is also these error tip
